text:
Hi Will,

  The major problem is the following:

        var node = document.createElement("text");

  This very common error results in a text node in the default (null) 
namespace if you want something to be rendered you need to create the 
text node in the SVG Namespace (you might want to read the FAQ):

var svg_ns = "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg";
[...]

        var node = document.createElementNS(svg_ns, "text");

--

  Also CVS Batik produces the error message at the bottom of this
response , in particular Batik complains about the line: 

        src: local("Harpoon"), url("harpoonn.ttf") format("truetype");

  There is no 'local(<string>)' allowed in the @font-face src descriptor. 
From CSS 2 specification:

’src’ (Descriptor)
Value: [ <uri> [format(<string> [, <string>]*)] | <font-face-name> ] [, <uri>
[format(<string> [, <string>]*)] | <font-face-name> ]*

   I think you want that line to be:

    src: "Harpoon", url("harpoonn.ttf") format("truetype")

(BTW did you notice that the harpoon in the url has an extra 'n'?

   This probably explains why your content isn't getting styled.
I will tenatively close this bug as I believe these minor corrections
in your content will have Batik rendering just like ASV.  If you
feel I am in error feel free to reopen the bug.


SVG Error:

http://odin.himinbi.org/covers/images/cover_template.svg?discname=test%20disc%20name&release=woody%201.2%20rc2&discid=1:
The following stylesheet represents an invalid 
CSS document.

      @font-face {
        font-family: harpoon;
        src: local("Harpoon"), url("harpoonn.ttf") format("truetype");
      }
      #discname, #release {
        font-size: 25;
        font-family: harpoon;
        filter: url(#emboss);
      }
      #discid {
        font-size: 200;
        opacity: .5;
        fill: red;
        text-anchor: middle;
        filter: url(#dropShadow);
      }

Original message:
The "src" property does not support function values.
